This paper discusses the evaluation of computational visual saliency models, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also involves the use of subjective ratings by human observers, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed metric is based on local weights, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and statistical analysis (cs.LG).
